Configuration.Admins.NewAdmin.Page1.Head: Welcome to the Ranking Creator
Configuration.Admins.NewAdmin.Page1.Body:
The Ranking Creator allows you to create new administrative rankings and specify their permitted apps and users. New users you add will be given access to Administer instantly even if already inside the game.
You'll only be able to add applications which you personally have access to. Only people with the permission will be able to enable the option to permit all apps.
Configuration.Admins.NewAdmin.Page2.Filt: Pick some details about the rank to make it easier to identify. The rank's name will be filtered, must be unique, and under 50 characters.
Configuration.Admins.NewAdmin.Page3.Page: Choose the members for this ranking. You can edit this later.
Configuration.Admins.NewAdmin.Page4.Page: Choose the applications and commands that this ranking will be able to see.
Configuration.Admins.NewAdmin.Page5.Body: Fantastic! Your ranking has been successfully created. Anybody you just added will be given the panel instantly. No need to do anything from here. If you would like to edit this rank in the future, come back to this page at any time and click the settings icon next to the name of the rank you have just created.
Configuration.Apps.Header.Desc: See the applications you have installed here, and enable/disable them. If they have settings, you can edit them too.

setting.Admins.CheckTime.Description: How often to check if admins are still admins, and take away the panel if they are not.
setting.Admins.AllowProtectedEdits.Descr: Allows editing protected rankings (superadmin). Also allows the creation of them. Not recommended as you could potentially break your installation.
setting.Interface.AnimationSpeed.Descrip: Controls the speed of client side animations. Higher is slower. Set to 0 to disable animations.
setting.Interface.DisableUnofficialAppWa: Hides the warning which says if a plugin is external. Useful for new people, otherwise just UI clutter.
setting.Interface.EnableEditableImages.D: Enables EditableImage features such as application card backgrounds, application card reflections, and other blurring effects. Does not disable "image glow". Currently nonfunctional outside of Studio due to Roblox limitations.
setting.Interface.HomepageGreeting.Descr: This is the text that displays after the "Good morning, username!" text on the homepage.
setting.Interface.PanelKeybind.Descripti: The key used to open the panel on keyboard-enabled devices.
setting.Interface.EnableClickEffects.Des: Increases memory usage slightly, also makes noise.
setting.Apps.LoadDelay.Description: Enables a 3s delay before loading any admins. Use this to solve applications not initializing.
setting.Apps.FetchAppServers.Description: Disallows Administer from contacting any external application servers.
setting.Apps.LoadApps.Description: Controls the ability for the server to load external applications. You shouldn't enable this unless you need a clean install or need to remove it.
setting.Accessibility.ChatCommand.Descri: Enables a /adm command to open Administer.
setting.Accessibility.DisplayHours.Descr: If enabled, hours will be displayed on all timestamps, may be ignored in some.
setting.Accessibility.ShortNumberDecimal: How many decimals to display next to short numbers. 2 -> 12.34k, 3 -> 12.345k, etc.
setting.Accessibility.TopbarPlus.Descrip: Enables a Topbar+ section that you can launch Administer and applications from.
Controls how big the mobile open gesture is from the right side. If the value is disabled you will need either the chat command or Topbar+ setting enabled.
setting.Miscellaneous.EditableImageRende: Enables a task.wait() call in EditableImage rendering calls. Can help reduce significant lag if present. WARNING: Makes client loading SIGNIFICANTLY slower.
setting.Miscellaneous.NotificationCloseT: Default waiting time to close the notification at. Can be overridden by notifications.
setting.Miscellaneous.SandboxMode.Descri: (studio-only) Gives all people who join the game ranking 1 (superadmin). Useful for setting up. Once your rankings are set up, you should turn this off. (also known as sudo)
setting.Miscellaneous.Verbose.Descriptio: Prints out general log data, useful for technical users or debugging. If enabled, it'll appear in the Log too.
